12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That §§ 5–514(b), 6–606.1(b),
13 and 11–522(a) of the Financial Institutions Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, shall
14 be construed to apply retroactively and shall be applied to and interpreted to affect any
15 conventional home mortgage loan entered into prior to the effective date of this Act. Any
16 conventional home mortgage that exceeds the lending limits set by the Federal Housing
17 Finance Agency entered into before the effective date of this Act shall be deemed to include
18 a provision allowing for any of the existing borrowers to purchase the property interest of
19 another borrower on the loan by assuming the seller’s portion of the mortgage in accordance
20 with Section 1 of this Act.
21 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That §§ 5–514(b), 6–606.1(b),
22 and 11–522(a) of the Financial Institutions Article, as enacted by Section 1 of this Act, shall
23 be construed to apply retroactively and shall be applied to and interpreted to affect any
24 conventional home mortgage loan entered into prior to the effective date of this Act. Any
25 conventional home mortgage that exceeds the lending limits set by the Federal Housing
26 Finance Agency entered into before the effective date of this Act shall be deemed to include a
27 provision allowing for any of the existing borrowers to purchase the property interest of
28 another borrower on the loan by assuming the seller’s portion of the mortgage under a decree
29 of absolute divorce entered into on or after the effective date of this Act and in accordance
30 with Section 1 of this Act.
31 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
32 October 1, 2025.

